know if you need to take it to a mechanic.

242
00:21:55,775 --> 00:21:57,367
You're sweet.

243
00:22:04,455 --> 00:22:07,925
- Remind me to offer to fix your car more often.
- (Laughs)

244
00:22:10,415 --> 00:22:12,451
- Hi, Mr Stanton.
- Hi, Angie.

245
00:22:15,015 --> 00:22:17,609
- Is that your boyfriend?
- No, just a friend.

246
00:22:17,655 --> 00:22:20,249
I had a little car trouble,
so he gave me a ride.

247
00:22:20,295 --> 00:22:21,489
Huh. Nice friend.

248
00:22:21,535 --> 00:22:23,332
Yeah. He is a nice friend.

249
00:22:23,375 --> 00:22:25,605
- Hm.
- (Honking)

250
00:22:30,815 --> 00:22:33,488
Is there any chance
you could give me a ride home?

251
00:22:33,535 --> 00:22:34,934
I don't see why not.

252
00:22:35,935 --> 00:22:38,324
Psst. (Come on up.)

253
00:22:38,375 --> 00:22:40,969
- Ah, here. I'll take that.
- Thanks.

254
00:22:52,295 --> 00:22:54,365
You weren't kidding
about the cowboy outfit.

255
00:22:54,415 --> 00:22:56,610
Like I said,
he never takes the thing off.

256
00:22:56,655 --> 00:22:59,294
You wouldn't believe what a pain it is
to get him to take a bath.

257
00:22:59,335 --> 00:23:00,848
(Laughs)

258
00:23:00,895 --> 00:23:03,887
Sam couldn't stop talking about you
after you left the other day.

259
00:23:03,935 --> 00:23:06,369
Really?
I wasn't sure he even liked me.

260
00:23:06,415 --> 00:23:08,406
- Oh, no, no, no, no, he loves you.
- Oh.

261
00:23:08,455 --> 00:23:11,367
It's just, you know, he gets very quiet
when he first meets people.

262
00:23:11,415 --> 00:23:12,643
Oh.

263
00:23:12,695 --> 00:23:15,892
OK, so let me just show you
a few things.

264
00:23:15,935 --> 00:23:17,926
Here is the TV remote.
Sam is a heavy sleeper,

265
00:23:17,975 --> 00:23:20,205
but you might want to keep it low,
just in case.

266
00:23:20,255 --> 00:23:23,884
And here is the phone with all the contact
numbers that you could possibly need.

267
00:23:23,935 --> 00:23:26,290
- Keys to the Jeep, in case you need it.
- Got it.

268
00:23:26,335 --> 00:23:28,803
Help yourself to anything
in the refrigerator,

269
00:23:28,855 --> 00:23:31,244
but the bottom row is Sam's.
He's on a special diet,

270
00:23:31,295 --> 00:23:33,889
so don't feed him anything
that's not in those containers,

271
00:23:33,935 --> 00:23:35,448
just in case he wakes up hungry.

272
00:23:35,495 --> 00:23:37,053
So, we all set?

273
00:23:37,095 --> 00:23:39,768
I think so. Are you sure
you don't have any questions?

274
00:23:39,815 --> 00:23:41,214
Oh, come on. She's fine.

275
00:23:41,255 --> 00:23:43,405
- We're running late anyway.
- OK, OK.

276
00:23:43,455 --> 00:23:46,333
- Do you have any idea when you'll be back?
- We shouldn't be gone

277
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:49,128
more than three or four hours.
Just make yourself at home.

278
00:23:49,175 --> 00:23:50,927
- We'll see you later.
- Have a good night.

279
00:23:50,975 --> 00:23:53,091
- OK, thanks.
- Don't forget to call.

280
00:24:46,615 --> 00:24:48,571
(Electrical static)

281
00:24:49,895 --> 00:24:51,487
(Electrical buzzing)

282
00:25:00,895 --> 00:25:02,613
(Flips switch on and off)

283
00:25:04,935 --> 00:25:09,486
Don't start playing games with yourself.
It's just an old house.

284
00:25:32,055 --> 00:25:33,454
(Beeps)

285
00:25:47,375 --> 00:25:50,685
- There's a heart attack waiting to happen.
- (Microwave pings)

286
00:26:03,735 --> 00:26:05,407
(Phone)

287
00:26:10,895 --> 00:26:12,806
- Hello?
<i>- Hi, it's me.</i>

288
00:26:12,855 --> 00:26:16,734
Hey there, me. How's the babysitting going?
The kid driving you crazy yet?

289
00:26:16,775 --> 00:26:19,767
- No, it's like he's not even here.
- <i>I guess that's good, right?</i>

290
00:26:19,815 --> 00:26:22,887
(Laughs) I just wanted to let you know
you don't have to come get me.

291
00:26:22,935 --> 00:26:24,493
Mr Stanton's gonna give me a ride.

292
00:26:24,535 --> 00:26:27,288
Oh. I was actually looking forward to it.

293
00:26:28,335 --> 00:26:32,726
In fact,
you called right at the moment of truth.

294
00:26:32,775 --> 00:26:34,174
(Engine starts)

295
00:26:34,215 --> 00:26:36,251
Oh, I'm good.

296
00:26:36,295 --> 00:26:40,527
<i>Your starter connection was bad. I took it apart,</i>
<i>put it back together and reconnected it.</i>

297
00:26:40,575 --> 00:26:42,133
<i>Thank you so much.</i>

298
00:26:42,175 --> 00:26:43,972
So, uh, I'll see you later?

299
00:26:44,015 --> 00:26:45,448
<i>OK, I'll see you later.</i>

300
00:26:50,015 --> 00:26:51,573
(Phone)

301
00:26:59,015 --> 00:27:02,132
- Stanton residence.
<i>- (Crackling/opera singing)</i>

302
00:27:02,175 --> 00:27:04,530
- Hello?
<i>- (Opera singing)</i>

303
00:27:04,575 --> 00:27:07,726
- Rick, is that you?
<i>- (Opera singing/crackling)</i>

304
00:27:07,775 --> 00:27:11,484
I'm sorry. Whoever this is, I can't hear you.
I'm gonna hang up now.

305
00:27:15,415 --> 00:27:17,212
(Ringing)

306
00:27:32,215 --> 00:27:34,285
- Hello?
<i>- (Crackling/opera singing)</i>

307
00:27:34,335 --> 00:27:35,734
<i>(Opera singing)</i>

308
00:27:39,255 --> 00:27:40,847
(Dial tone)

309
00:27:46,975 --> 00:27:49,091
- (Ringing)
- <i>That was fast.</i>

310
00:27:49,135 --> 00:27:50,534
Did you just try calling me?

311
00:27:50,575 --> 00:27:52,088
No.

312
00:27:52,135 --> 00:27:54,410
- <i>Oh. OK.</i>
- Are you OK?

313
00:27:54,455 --> 00:27:57,527
I'm fine. Someone just tried calling,
and I thought it might be you.

314
00:27:57,575 --> 00:27:59,054
No, wasn't me.

315
00:27:59,095 --> 00:28:01,245
OK, well, I will call you later.

316
00:28:01,295 --> 00:28:02,694
<i>OK.</i>

317
00:28:05,615 --> 00:28:07,606
<i>(Opera singing)</i>

318
00:28:19,575 --> 00:28:21,372
Maybe a little TV will help.

319
00:28:25,695 --> 00:28:29,768
<i>(Loud TV) Woo-woo-woo-woo, ha-ha!</i>
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, thank you very much.</i>

320
00:28:29,815 --> 00:28:31,646
<i>Thank you...</i>

321
00:28:31,695 --> 00:28:34,163
It would be a good idea
not to leave it on at full volume,

322
00:28:34,215 --> 00:28:36,854
if you don't want it played too loud.

323
00:28:36,895 --> 00:28:39,125
I hope that didn't wake him.

324
00:28:39,175 --> 00:28:42,008
<i>(Opera singing)</i>

325
00:28:43,975 --> 00:28:45,374
<i>(Singing stops)</i>

326
00:28:47,055 --> 00:28:48,647
(Door opening and closing)

327
00:29:08,655 --> 00:29:10,293
He does sleep like a rock.

328
00:29:11,735 --> 00:29:13,487
(Tinkling)

329
00:29:15,895 --> 00:29:17,294
(Tinkling continues)

330
00:29:36,255 --> 00:29:38,291
(Door creaks)

331
00:29:39,295 --> 00:29:40,694
(Chimes)

332
00:30:00,135 --> 00:30:01,693
(Gasps)

333
00:30:02,375 --> 00:30:04,286
Oh, God, you scared me.

334
00:30:05,255 --> 00:30:07,166
I'm sorry, did I wake you up?

335
00:30:07,215 --> 00:30:08,933
Hungry.

336
00:30:08,975 --> 00:30:12,684
Oh. OK, let's go get
you something to eat.

337
00:30:25,415 --> 00:30:28,009
Your mom said you can
only eat the food on the bottom...

338
00:30:29,935 --> 00:30:31,732
You want me to heat some of this up?

339
00:30:41,335 --> 00:30:46,011
Diced red meat.
Very rare diced red meat.

340
00:30:47,015 --> 00:30:48,926
Let's get a different one.

341
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:57,489
I guess it's diced rare meat.

342
00:31:14,055 --> 00:31:16,011
- (Microwave pings)
- (Sizzling)

343
00:31:21,095 --> 00:31:23,609
Are you sure
you're supposed to have this?

344
00:31:25,215 --> 00:31:26,534
OK.

345
00:31:32,135 --> 00:31:33,932
Do you want some ketchup
or something?

346
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,966
Careful, you're gonna burn your...

347
00:31:54,535 --> 00:31:56,173
(Phone)

348
00:32:10,175 --> 00:32:11,574
Hello?

349
00:32:14,295 --> 00:32:15,967
Please stop calling here.

350
00:32:28,935 --> 00:32:31,130
(Door handle rattles)

351
00:32:31,175 --> 00:32:32,893
Did you hear that?

352
00:33:00,575 --> 00:33:02,088
(Rattles handle)

353
00:33:12,855 --> 00:33:14,208
(Rattles handle)

354
00:33:35,495 --> 00:33:37,292
(Rattles handle)

355
00:33:46,215 --> 00:33:47,614
(Phone)

356
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:52,286
Good evening, Montague Dispatch.

357
00:33:53,695 --> 00:33:55,094
One moment, please.

358
00:33:55,775 --> 00:33:58,335
Chief... Line one.

359
00:33:59,575 --> 00:34:02,931
- Dinneli here.
<i>- Hi, this is Angie. I came by your office today.</i>

360
00:34:02,975 --> 00:34:04,966
Oh, yeah.
Hi, Angie, how you doin'?

361
00:34:05,015 --> 00:34:08,530
<i>I'm not sure. I'm babysitting at
seven-twenty-four Lancaster Road.</i>

362
00:34:08,575 --> 00:34:12,170
- That's the Stanton place. I know it.
- I think there's someone outside the house.

363
00:34:12,215 --> 00:34:13,443
<i>Did you see someone?</i>

364
00:34:13,495 --> 00:34:15,963
Not exactly.
I just keep hearing strange noises,

365
00:34:16,015 --> 00:34:18,734
and I keep getting
these phone calls where no one talks.

366
00:34:18,775 --> 00:34:22,085
- How would you describe the noises?
- I don't know. Like locks rattling,

367
00:34:22,135 --> 00:34:24,968
- like there's someone outside the door.
- Angie, calm down.

368
00:34:25,015 --> 00:34:27,324
Now, did you see someone outside?

369
00:34:27,375 --> 00:34:29,331
No, it just feels like there is.

370
00:34:29,375 --> 00:34:34,130
OK, well, I'm just about to make my rounds,
so I will swing by and check it out, OK?

371
00:34:34,175 --> 00:34:35,574
Thank you.

372
00:34:43,655 --> 00:34:45,327
Sam?

373
00:34:48,975 --> 00:34:50,613
Sam?

374
00:34:54,495 --> 00:34:56,884
- Sam?
- (Footstep)

375
00:35:09,135 --> 00:35:11,126
(Laughter)

376
00:35:18,095 --> 00:35:19,847
Sam, are you getting back in bed?

377
00:35:19,895 --> 00:35:24,286
I think you should brush
your teeth... first.

378
00:35:38,935 --> 00:35:40,493
Sam?

379
00:35:45,135 --> 00:35:46,648
Where are you?

380
00:36:01,855 --> 00:36:03,527
Are you playing a game with me?

381
00:36:13,415 --> 00:36:17,647
Come on, Sam! I need you to get back
in bed before your parents get home.

382
00:36:17,695 --> 00:36:19,492
(Laughter)

383
00:36:19,535 --> 00:36:22,891
Hey, buddy, where are you goin'?

384
00:36:34,695 --> 00:36:36,174
Sam?

385
00:36:51,535 --> 00:36:53,048
(Door creaking)

386
00:37:24,655 --> 00:37:26,247
Sam!

387
00:37:28,455 --> 00:37:32,289
Sam, I'm done playing now, OK?
You have to get in bed.

388
00:37:36,375 --> 00:37:39,526
I'm serious. This isn't funny.
You need to go to sleep.

389
00:37:52,575 --> 00:37:53,974
Sam?

390
00:37:59,415 --> 00:38:01,690
(Lights buzz)

391
00:38:06,535 --> 00:38:08,253
Sam, are you in here?

392
00:38:13,415 --> 00:38:15,770
It's past your bedtime.

393
00:38:17,415 --> 00:38:20,487
Your mommy is gonna be
very, very upset with you.

394
00:38:26,815 --> 00:38:28,487
Do you hear me, young man?

395
00:38:32,695 --> 00:38:34,447
(Screams)

396
00:38:37,735 --> 00:38:39,134
(Phone)

397
00:38:46,495 --> 00:38:47,894
Hello?

398
00:38:48,975 --> 00:38:50,374
Who is this?

399
00:38:56,375 --> 00:38:58,684
(Phone)

400
00:38:58,735 --> 00:39:01,203
Hey, you ruined my surprise.
I'm about 20 minutes away.

401
00:39:01,255 --> 00:39:03,530
Oh, thank God!
I'm freaking out right now.

402
00:39:03,575 --> 00:39:05,930
- Hey, why, what's wrong?
<i>- This guy keeps calling,</i>

403
00:39:05,975 --> 00:39:09,126
<i>the kid is playing hide-and-seek</i>
<i>and the house is making strange noises.</i>

404
00:39:09,175 --> 00:39:10,893
- Whoa. Angie, slow down.
- (Horn)

405
00:39:12,295 --> 00:39:13,887
What's your problem, buddy?

406
00:39:14,895 --> 00:39:17,568
Hey, Angie, I gotta pull
over for a second. Hold on.

407
00:39:17,615 --> 00:39:19,014
(Horn)

408
00:39:21,215 --> 00:39:23,775
Rick? Hello?

409
00:39:23,815 --> 00:39:26,283
- (Dial tone)
- (Whispers) Oh great.

410
00:39:28,895 --> 00:39:30,453
(Rattling)

411
00:39:40,455 --> 00:39:42,491
(Rattles and thuds)

412
00:39:44,055 --> 00:39:45,283
(Screams)

413
00:39:45,335 --> 00:39:47,166
- (Rattles and thuds)
- (Screams)

414
00:39:47,855 --> 00:39:49,254
(Gasps)

415
00:41:31,575 --> 00:41:33,054
(Laughter)

416
00:41:48,495 --> 00:41:49,894
(Clattering)

417
00:41:51,535 --> 00:41:52,968
I need a weapon.

418
00:42:56,935 --> 00:42:58,334
(Footsteps approach)

419
00:43:39,655 --> 00:43:41,054
(Door creaks)

420
00:43:50,495 --> 00:43:52,247
- (Grunts)
- Ahh!

421
00:43:55,255 --> 00:43:56,654
Sam?

422
00:43:57,415 --> 00:43:59,053
Sam, wait!

423
00:44:02,975 --> 00:44:04,454
(Screams)

424
00:44:04,495 --> 00:44:08,124
Help, somebody!
Let go of me!

425
00:44:08,175 --> 00:44:09,403
(Grunts)

426
00:44:11,335 --> 00:44:12,563
(Vase shattering)

427
00:44:24,415 --> 00:44:25,814
(Glass breaking)

428
00:44:38,775 --> 00:44:42,688
Sam? Sam, where are you?!

429
00:44:44,295 --> 00:44:47,446
Sam, come on, we have to go!
(Whimpers)

430
00:44:48,935 --> 00:44:50,288
Sam!

431
00:44:58,175 --> 00:45:01,247
Sam, please, I know you're scared.

432
00:45:06,215 --> 00:45:09,287
Look, I'm scared, too, Sam,
but we have to go.

433
00:45:12,775 --> 00:45:14,367
- Sam, please!
- (Clatter)

434
00:45:14,415 --> 00:45:16,133
(Screams)

435
00:45:16,615 --> 00:45:18,207
(Cries)

436
00:45:19,295 --> 00:45:21,286
Why? (Sobs)

437
00:45:23,415 --> 00:45:25,292
(Creaking)

438
00:45:25,335 --> 00:45:26,529
Oh.

439
00:45:26,575 --> 00:45:28,247
Oh, Sam, thank God!

440
00:45:29,615 --> 00:45:32,413
I need you to come with me, OK?
Come on.

441
00:45:37,415 --> 00:45:38,814
Come on.

442
00:45:40,695 --> 00:45:43,163
- We're just gonna go for a little drive, OK?
- Hungry.

443
00:45:43,215 --> 00:45:46,412
I know. We'll get you something
to eat later, OK, sweetie?

444
00:45:48,615 --> 00:45:51,209
Oh no, I left the keys in the house.

445
00:45:52,215 --> 00:45:55,173
OK, we're just gonna run inside,
we're gonna grab the keys,

446
00:45:55,215 --> 00:45:57,092
and we're gonna get out of here, OK?

447
00:46:01,815 --> 00:46:03,646
(Door creaking)

448
00:46:14,735 --> 00:46:16,293
(It's gonna be OK.)

449
00:46:18,455 --> 00:46:22,687
Sam, I need you to wait here
until I get back, OK? OK?

450
00:46:23,535 --> 00:46:25,093
Wait here.

451
00:47:00,455 --> 00:47:03,288
- (Screams) Evil! Evil!
- Sam, run!

452
00:47:03,335 --> 00:47:06,486
- Evil! Ah! Evil! (Groans)
- (Screams)

453
00:47:06,535 --> 00:47:08,844
- Run!
- (Growls)

454
00:47:08,895 --> 00:47:10,886
(Growls)

455
00:47:14,335 --> 00:47:15,848
- Stay away from him!
- (Grunts)

456
00:47:16,575 --> 00:47:18,406
(Groans)

457
00:47:18,455 --> 00:47:23,165
Evil! Evil! Evil!

458
00:47:23,215 --> 00:47:24,614
(Groans)

459
00:47:24,655 --> 00:47:26,293
(Gasps)

460
00:47:27,295 --> 00:47:30,367
- (Grunts) Evil!
- (Groans)

461
00:47:30,415 --> 00:47:32,167
Let go! (Grunts)

462
00:47:32,215 --> 00:47:33,887
- (Moans, gasps)
- (Grunts)

463
00:47:34,815 --> 00:47:36,294
(Groans)

464
00:47:52,895 --> 00:47:54,692
Sam, are you all right?

465
00:48:14,895 --> 00:48:17,250
(Oh, my God!)

466
00:48:17,295 --> 00:48:18,887
Hungry.

467
00:48:23,175 --> 00:48:24,654
God help me.

468
00:48:24,695 --> 00:48:26,765
(Gasps)

469
00:48:35,175 --> 00:48:36,449
Oh, my God, Sam, no.

470
00:48:36,495 --> 00:48:38,565
Oh, God, baby, are you OK?

471
00:48:38,615 --> 00:48:40,492
Another goddamn priest.

472
00:48:43,255 --> 00:48:45,530
Son of a bitch,
this is Father Nicoletta!

473
00:48:45,575 --> 00:48:48,487
- Thought I killed that fucker in Romania.
- Well, I guess you didn't.

474
00:48:48,535 --> 00:48:50,014
You are one tough old bastard.

475
00:48:50,055 --> 00:48:53,491
Last time I saw you, you had an axe
stickin' out of the top of your head.

476
00:48:53,535 --> 00:48:55,890
- Jim, how did he find us?
- I don't know. Goddamn!

477
00:48:55,935 --> 00:48:57,926
(Groans)

478
00:48:57,975 --> 00:49:01,172
Oh, oh, that's just great.
He's still alive. Just great!

479
00:49:01,215 --> 00:49:04,525
- (Moans)
- Come on, baby, let's get out of here.

480
00:49:04,575 --> 00:49:06,611
- (Groans)
- (Whimpers)

481
00:49:08,455 --> 00:49:10,844
Well, he's dead now.
They're like fuckin' rats.

482
00:49:12,455 --> 00:49:15,015
- (Whimpers)
- Ohh!

483
00:49:16,055 --> 00:49:18,489
Hold on there, Missy.

484
00:49:18,535 --> 00:49:20,446
You're not going anywhere.

485
00:49:22,975 --> 00:49:24,374
Sorry.

486
00:49:24,855 --> 00:49:26,083
(Thud)

487
00:49:26,695 --> 00:49:28,526
(Scrubbing sound)

488
00:49:31,935 --> 00:49:34,085
Vi... Stop.

489
00:49:35,495 --> 00:49:37,690
We covered our tracks so well.

